m%20chance%20the%20star%20could%20pull%20the%20Earth%20to%20a%20more%20habitable%20zone%2C%20a%20study%20suggested.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20around%20a%20billion%20years%2C%20the%20sun%20will%20become%20hot%20enough%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsun-destroy-earth-red-giant-white-dwarf-2016-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20boil%20all%20the%20oceans%20on%20our%20planet%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20life%20as%20we%20know%20it%20will%20be%20destroyed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fate%20of%20life%20on%20Earth%2C%20scientists%20think%2C%20is%20more%20or%20less%20sealed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20a%20passing%20star%20could%20prove%20to%20be%20an%20unlikely%20savior%2C%20according%20to%20a%20new%20study%20by%20scientists%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Bordeaux%2C%20France%2C%20and%20the%20Planetary%20Science%20Institute%20in%20Tucson%2C%20Arizona.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20ran%2012%2C000%20simulations%20to%20see%20what%20would%20happen%20if%20a%20star%20passed%20within%20100%20astronomical%20units%20(about%209.3%20billion%20miles)%20from%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20simulations%20showed%20that%20our%20solar%20system%20is%20remarkably%20stable.%20In%2092%25%20of%20cases%2C%20the%20solar%20system%20would%20remain%20almost%20intact%20even%20as%20a%20star%20passed%20by%20the%20solar%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20thought%20more%20would%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Sean%20Raymond%2C%20a%20study%20author%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Bordeaux%20in%20France%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newscientist.com%2Farticle%2F2405706-passing-star-could-fling-earth-out-past-pluto-into-the-oort-cloud%2F%3Futm_campaign%3DRSS%257CNSNS%26utm_source%3DNSNS%26utm_medium%3DRSS%26utm_content%3Dnews%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20Scientist%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20not%20that%20easy%20to%20mess%20with%20planets'%20orbits%20%E2%80%93%20a%20star%20has%20to%20get%20really%20into%20another%20star's%20business%20to%20mess%20with%20its%20planets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20there's%20a%20chance%20the%20passing%20star%20could%20pull%20our%20planet%20out%20of%20harm's%20way%20%E2%80%94%20albeit%20a%20slim%20one.%20In%200.28%25%20of%20the%20simulations%2C%20the%20star%20pulled%20the%20Earth%20out%20of%20its%20orbit%20and%20into%20a%20more%20temperate%20region%2C%20Raymond%20said%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplanetplanet.net%2F2023%2F11%2F21%2Fcould-a-stellar-flyby-save-earth-from-impending-doom%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20blog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20manifested%20in%20a%20number%20of%20ways.%20In%20some%20simulations%2C%20Earth%20remained%20in%20the%20solar%20system%20but%20was%20pulled%20to%20a%20region%20beyond%20Pluto%20that's%20about%2010%25%20cooler%20than%20our%20current%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20simulations%2C%20Earth%20was%20kicked%20into%20interstellar%20space%2C%20ending%20up%20in%20the%20Oort%20cloud%2C%20about%202%20billion%20light%20years%20away%2C%20or%20as%20a%20free-floating%20planet%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20bizarre%20as%20it%20might%20seem%2C%20this%20may%20not%20be%20the%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplanetplanet.net%2F2023%2F11%2F21%2Fcould-a-stellar-flyby-save-earth-from-impending-doom%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaymond%20in%20a%20blog%20post%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20much%20harder%20to%20un-roast%20a%20fried%20planet%20than%20to%20heat%20up%20a%20frozen%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20they%20possess%20modestly%20thick%20hydrogen%20atmospheres%2C%20free-floating%20planets%20can%20trap%20enough%20heat%20to%20maintain%20liquid%20water%20on%20the%20surface%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20also%20a%20few%20scenarios%20where%20the%20star%20captured%20the%20Earth%20as%20it%20flew%20by.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20scenarios%20where%20the%20Earth%20was%20taken%20away%20from%20the%20broiling%20zone%2C%20it%20wasn't%20automatically%20saved.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20it%20ended%20up%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmoon-formation-giant-impact-earth-synestia-2018-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrashing%20into%20the%20moon%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Venus.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20only%20a%201%25%20chance%20a%20star%20could%20fly%20by%20our%20solar%20system%20in%20the%20next%20billion%20years%2C%20and%20the%20simulations%20predict%20a%201%20in%20350%20chance%20of%20Earth%20being%20kicked%20into%20a%20habitable%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20taken%20together%2C%20%26quot%3Bthat's%20a%201%20in%2035%2C000%20chance%20that%20the%20long-term%20prospects%20for%20life%20on%20Earth%20will%20be%20rescued%20by%20a%20passing%20star%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Raymond%20in%20a%20blog%20post.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20about%20the%20same%20odds%20as%20randomly%20pulling%20the%20ace%20of%20spades%20from%20two%20separate%20decks%20of%20cards%20while%20also%20rolling%20a%20combined%2010%20with%20two%20dice.%20Not%20the%20best%20odds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20findings%20were%20published%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Facademic.oup.com%2Fmnras%2Fadvance-article%2Fdoi%2F10.1093%2Fmnras%2Fstad3604%2F7452883%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMonthly%20Notices%20of%20the%20Royal%20Astronomical%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20November%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frogue-star-save-earth-extinction-knocking-it-past-pluto-raymond-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701776735000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F656f00690ec98e92f74c0b94%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frogue-star-save-earth-extinction-knocking-it-past-pluto-raymond-2023-12%22%2C%22summar