ally%20in%20corporate%20America.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20generations%20are%20forming%20a%20new%20culture%20of%20work%20where%20their%20comfort%20is%20paramount%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-millennials-and-gen-z-dont-want-to-be-managers-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclimbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder%20isn't%20a%20priority%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20TikTok%20videos%2C%20many%20discuss%20their%20lack%20of%20trust%20in%20senior%20leadership%2C%20the%20limited%20financial%20reward%20of%20management%2C%20and%20their%20greater%20focus%20on%20a%20work-life%20balance%20and%20time%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20result%20could%20be%20that%20the%20amount%20of%20people%20putting%20themselves%20forward%20for%20incremental%20middle%20management%20roles%20dwindles%2C%20with%20young%20workers%20focusing%20on%20other%20pursuits%2C%20or%20waiting%20longer%20to%20go%20for%20more%20senior%20titles%20when%20they%20become%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20may%20even%20be%20that%20Gen%20Z%20kills%20off%20middle%20management%20for%20good.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ESuccess%20looks%20different%20to%20Gen%20Z%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20Voyer%2C%20an%20ESCP%20Business%20School%20professor%20and%20founder%20of%20the%20Gen%20Z%20Observatory%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20his%20research%20showed%20that%20%26quot%3Bsuccess%20takes%20many%20more%20different%20forms%26quot%3B%20for%20Gen%20Z%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20real%20disconnection%20between%20succeeding%20and%20it%20being%20work-based%20for%20previous%20generation%20and%20what%20Gen%20Z%20sees%20as%20success%2C%20which%20is%20a%20much%20more%2C%20better%20rounded%2C%20360%20%5Bdegree%5D%20form%20of%20success%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20it's%20really%20not%20just%20about%20getting%20very%20fast%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20company%2C%20but%20it's%20rather%20about%20being%20able%20to%20achieve%20work-life%20balance%20and%20being%20able%20to%20have%20a%20good%20job%2C%20and%20also%20making%20meaningful%20contributions%20outside%20of%20your%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20recent%20survey%20of%201%2C000%20US%20workers%20by%20software%20company%20Visier%20even%20found%20that%20less%20than%20half%20%E2%80%94%2038%25%20%E2%80%94%20said%20they%20want%20to%20become%20managers%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhy-millennials-and-gen-z-dont-want-to-be-managers-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBI%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%2073%25%20of%20workers%20are%20willing%20to%20take%20a%20pay%20cut%20or%20step%20down%20from%20their%20current%20position%20to%20pursue%20a%20more%20fulfilling%20career%20path%2C%20a%20recent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-like-to-job-hop-change-career-survey-2023-11%3Fr%3DUS%26IR%3DT%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%20by%20Resource%20Solutions%20found%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMichelle%20P.%20King%2C%20Netflix's%20former%20director%20of%20diversity%20and%20inclusion%20and%20an%20award-winning%20academic%20and%20author%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20Gen%20Z%20are%20looking%20at%20their%20managers%20and%20thinking%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20aspire%20to%20be%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20what%20they're%20doing%2C%20it's%20actually%20how%20they're%20doing%20it%20that's%20turning%20people%20off%20and%20I%20think%20the%20major%20reason%20why%20is%20that%20the%20way%20managers%20manage%20actually%20breaks%20trust%2C%26quot%3B%20King%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20explained%20that%20although%20people%20are%20being%20paid%20which%20holds%20up%20one%20end%20of%20the%20bargain%20at%20work%2C%20their%20experience%20of%20work%20isn't%20so%20great.%20Most%20people's%20%26quot%3Bprimary%20needs%20at%20work%20are%20not%20being%20met%26quot%3B%20by%20managers%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reason%20they%20probably%20don't%20aspire%20to%20the%20manager%20role%20is%20because%2C%20why%20should%20they%3F%20%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20work%20in%20a%20workplace%20where%20they%20don't%20trust%20the%20people%20they're%20working%20for.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMiddle%20management%20is%20a%20'tough%20spot'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWendy%20said%20seeing%20so%20many%20people%20discuss%20their%20work%20lives%2C%20and%20what%20they%20expected%20and%20no%20longer%20tolerated%20from%20a%20job%20on%20social%20media%20was%20eye%20opening.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20makes%20me%20feel%20a%20little%20bit%20more%20valid%2C%20or%20seen%2C%20because%20then%20it%20makes%20me%20think%20to%20myself%2C%20OK%2C%20I'm%20not%20being%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20happening%20to%20me%20is%20not%20me%20being%20dramatic%20or%20crazy%20or%20overthinking%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMorgan%20Sanner%2C%20who%20is%20a%20Gen%20Z%20founder%20of%20her%20own%20resume%20writing%20company%2C%20is%20one%20such%20social%20media%20poster.%20She%20speaks%20about%20career%20progression%20and%20this%20generational%20shift%20away%20from%20management%20in%20detail%20on%20her%20TikTok%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20told%20BI%20young%20workers%20in%20her%20generation%20tend%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bpurpose%20driven%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20something%20they%20think%20a%20lot%20of%20middle%20management%20positions%20may%20not%20provide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20they%20can't%20find%20a%20reason%20that%20they're%20do%20something%20or%20they're%20realizing%20that%20their%20work%20isn't%20actually%20impacting%20anyone%2C%20they're%20not%20interested%20in%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanner%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20unfortunately%20that%20is%20kind%20of%20what%20the%20middle%20manager%20role%20has%20become.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiddle%20management%20can%20also%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Btough%20spot%26quot%3B%20to%20be%20in%2C%20Sanner%20said%2C%20because%20they're%20seen%20as%20roles%20that%20are%20provided%20only%20moderate%20benefits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20seems%20like%20the%20employees%20like%20to%20blame%20the%20middle%20managers%2C%20and%20the%20leadership%20likes%20to%20blame%20middle%20managers%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20don't%20really%20get%20that%20much%20of%20a%20say%20in%20the%20decisions%20that%20they're%20making.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoyer%20emphasized%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20problem%20with%20traditional%20middle%20management%20is%20that%20it's%20just%20a%20waiting%20room%20for%20what%20most%20people%20hope%20will%20be%20an%20even%20higher%20C-suite%20position.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%3A%20%26quot%3BMiddle%20management%20is%20when%20you%20start%20having%20the%20burden%20of%20managing%20people%2C%20but%20you%20don't%20really%20have%20the%20big%20reward.%20So%20in%20terms%20of%20working%20out%20whether%20it's%20worth%20it%2C%20this%20is%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20Gen%20Z%20would%20rather%20be%20directly%20at%20the%20top.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20pointed%20out%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20his%20Gen%20Z%20students%20are%20looking%20to%20entrepreneurship%20to%20solve%20this%20issue%2C%20and%20hope%20to%20start%20their%20own%20businesses%20where%20they%20can%20actually%20make%20a%20meaningful%20contribution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAI%20might%20play%20a%20role%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESanner%20thinks%20AI%20might%20make%20some%20middle%20management%20roles%20redundant.%20Having%20worked%20with%20people%20in%20middle%20management%20positions%2C%20she%20can%20recall%20times%20where%20she%20thought%20to%20herself%20some%20of%20their%20work%20days%20seemed%20like%20a%20waste%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20of%20the%20stuff%20they%20were%20doing%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20man%2C%20there's%20got%20to%20be%20a%20better%20way%20to%20do%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVoyer%20agrees%20with%20this%20view%20saying%20that%20one%20possible%20outcome%20of%20Gen%20Z%20rejecting%20middle%20management%20roles%20is%20that%20it%20%26quot%3Bwill%20be%20good%20for%20the%20AI%20revolution%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20change%20what%20kind%20of%20jobs%20are%20in%20demand.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20people%20are%20claiming%20that%20one%20of%20the%20risks%20of%20AI%20at%20work%20is%20the%20disappearance%20of%20middle%20management%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20explained.%20%26quot%3BYou'll%20need%20very%20high%20%5Blevel%5D%C2%A0%20people%20who%20know%20how%20to%20navigate%20all%20these%20tools%20and%20so%20on.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20survey%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Famericanstaffing.net%2Fposts%2F2023%2F08%2F17%2Fhow-ai-will-affect-employment%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EAmerican%20Staffing%20Association%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20Harris%20Poll%20of%202%2C000%20adults%20in%20the%20US%20in%20August%20found%20that%2044%25%20of%20those%20in%20managerial%20or%20professional%20roles%20feel%20that%20automation%20could%20easily%20replace%20their%20jobs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F07%2F26%2Fwhich-u-s-workers-are-more-exposed-to-ai-on-their-jobs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EPew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20July%20found%20that%20jobs%20in%20high-paying%20fields%20that%20require%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20or%20more%20as%20well%20as%20analytical%20skills%20are%20more%20exposed%20and%20at%20risk%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWorking%20smarter%2C%20not%20harder%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20common%20critique%20of%20young%20workers%20entering%20the%20workforce%20with%20this%20opinion%20is%20that%20they%20are%20lazy%20or%20unambitious.%20After%20all%2C%20they%20coined%20the%20term%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flazy-girl-job-trend-tiktok-explained-defending-low-stress-work-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elazy%20girl%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20and%20have%20emphasized%20the%20benefits%20of%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-quiet-quitting-work-ethic-millennials-money-struggles-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equiet%20quitting%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20impression%20is%20wrong%2C%20though%2C%20Sanner%20said%2C%20with%20many%20Gen%20Zers%20and%20millennials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fside-hustle-ugc-delivery-make-money-flexible-time-easy-jobs-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehaving%20side%20hustles%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-millennial-workplace-trends-labor-job-market-side-hustle-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esecond%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey're%20not%20work-shy%2C%20it%20just%20happens%20to%20be%20the%20place%20they're%20putting%20all%20their%20extra%20energy%20isn't%20necessarily%20their%209-5.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20it%20comes%20off%20that%20they're%20entitled%20and%20lazy%20when%20really%20they're%20just%20trying%20to%20fix%20a%20process%20that%20might%20be%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20Sanner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESanner%20herself%2C%20for%20example%2C%20has%20always%20been%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20career%20driven%2C%26quot%3B%20doing%20five%20internships%20during%20her%20undergraduate%20degree%2C%20then%20getting%20her%20master's.%20But%20even%20she%20has%20become%20disillusioned%20to%20the%20idea%20of%20working%20at%20a%20company%20for%20three%20decades%2C%20getting%20a%20small%20step%20up%20every%20few%20years%2C%20then%20retiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20traditional%20advice%20of%20work%20really%20hard%20in%20your%20twenties%20and%20they'll%20pay%20off%20later%20down%20the%20line%20is%20not%20something%20that%20these%20generations%20are%20interested%20in%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20work%20really%20hard%20for%2030%20years%2C%20then%20I%20can%20relax.%20That's%20a%20little%20too%20long.%20A%20little%20too%20much%20of%20an%20investment.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKing%20also%20agreed%20that%20Gen%20Z%20rejecting%20middle%20management%20is%20not%20because%20they're%20work-averse%20or%20lazy.%20Instead%20it's%20because%20leadership%20roles%20haven't%20adapted%20to%20modern%20times%20and%20so%20they're%20so%20%26quot%3Bno%20thanks%2C%26quot%3B%20to%20what%20they're%20seeing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%20that%20the%20view%20of%20managers%20today%20is%20very%20much%20that%20old%20school%2C%201950s%20transactional%20command%20and%20control%20manager%20where%20you're%20telling%20others%20what%20to%20do%20and%20doing%20work%20yourself%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%20people%20don't%20need%20to%20be%20told%20what%20to%20do.%20They%20need%20managers%20who%20can%20manage%20how%20people%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20providing%20mentorship%2C%20coaching%2C%20feedback%2C%20delegating%2C%20and%20helping%20people%20to%20collaborate%20and%20solve%20problems%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20is%20most%20managers%20aren't.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIronically%2C%20millennials%20and%20Gen%20Z%20would%20be%20great%20managers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELynn%20said%20she%20thinks%20the%20shift%20away%20from%20management%20is%20a%20generational%20thing.%20Her%20older%20colleagues%2C%20for%20example%2C%20don't%20seem%20to%20be%20of%20the%20same%20opinion%2C%20and%20appear%20more%20content%20with%20the%20status%20quo.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20shame%20if%20younger%20workers%20don't%20become%20managers%2C%20she%20added%2C%20because%20the%20millennial%20who%20she%20works%20for%20right%20now%20is%20one%20of%20the%20best%20she's%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20very%20unserious%20in%20a%20good%20way.%20They%20call%20it%20as%20it%20is%20and%20they%20don't%20take%20everything%20so%20seriously%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20just%20very%20refreshing%20to%20have%20a%20manager%20who%20gets%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELooking%20at%20her%20own%20career%20progression%2C%20though%2C%20she's%20not%20sure%20she'll%20follow%20suit.%20She%20once%20had%20aspirations%20to%20be%20a%20senior%20director.%20Now%2C%20she's%20not%20so%20convinced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20ambition%20anymore%2C%20but%20I%20do%20just%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20ambition%20to%20optimize%20other%20parts%20of%20my%20life%20and%20I%20want%20to%20prioritize%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20we're%20lucky%20to%20realize%20that%20so%20young.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-might-kill-middle-management-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701775777000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6554a75136d588dc55d09297%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-might-kill-middle-management-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Young%20workers%20are%20turning%20their%20backs%20on%20management%20and%20climbing%20the%20corporate%20ladder.%20So%20much%20so%2C%20Gen%20Z%20might%20kill%20off%20the%20middle%20manager%20position.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ldodgson%40insider.com%20(Lindsay%20Dodgson%2CSawdah%20Bhaimiya)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-might-kill-middle-management-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22An%20airline%20passenger%20was%20escorted%20away%20by%20police%20after%20sparking%20a%20fight%20in%20the%20aisle%20and%20'demanding%20drinks'%20from%20flight%20attendants%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Scoot%20Boeing%20787-9%20Dreamliner%20taking%20off%20from%20Osaka%20-%20Kansai%20Airport.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D