al%20epaulettes%2C%20which%20is%20exclusively%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20IN%E2%80%99s%20Controller%20of%20Personnel%20Services%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20retired%20naval%20officer.%20It%20is%20also%20obvious%2C%20he%20regretfully%20added%2C%20that%20the%20IN%E2%80%99s%20top%20brass%20were%20complicit%20in%20this%20endeavour%2C%20and%20in%20all%20likelihood%20connived%20and%20even%20encouraged%20it%20to%20earn%20government%20approval.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EModi%E2%80%99s%20proclamation%20is%20part%20of%20a%20wider%20agenda%20of%20%E2%80%98deracinating%E2%80%99%20the%20navy%20by%20ditching%20all%20association%20dating%20back%20to%20its%20founding%20as%20the%20Royal%20Indian%20Navy%20or%20RIN%20in%201932%2C%20and%20entails%20infusing%20Shivaji%E2%80%99s%2017th-century%20octagonal%20stamp%20in%20place%20of%20the%20ubiquitous%20Nelson%E2%80%99s%20ring%20on%20uniform%20epaulettes%20inherited%20from%20the%20Royal%20Navy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInspired%20by%20the%20ideals%20of%20Shivaji%2C%20today%E2%80%99s%20India%20is%20moving%20forward%20and%20abandoning%20the%20mentality%20of%20slavery%2C%E2%80%9D%20Modi%20declared%20at%20the%20Navy%20Day%20function%20in%20Maharashtra%20on%20Monday.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20happy%20to%20announce%20that%20the%20epaulettes%20donned%20by%20the%20naval%20officers%20will%20now%20highlight%20the%20heritage%20and%20legacy%20of%20Shivaji%20and%20they%20will%20be%20similar%20to%20the%20naval%20ensign%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20September%2C%20Shivaji%E2%80%99s%20octagonal%20stamp%2C%20symbolising%20India%E2%80%99s%20hoary%20maritime%20heritage%2C%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fhow-the-indian-navys-ensign-evolved-over-the-years%5C%22%3Ereplaced%20the%20Cross%20of%20St%20George%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20IN%E2%80%99s%20ensign%20or%20flag%20as%20part%20of%20%E2%80%98the%20military%E2%80%99s%20de-colonisation%E2%80%99%20launched%20recently%20by%20the%20BJP-led%20Union%20government.%20Around%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20IN%20had%20also%20discontinued%20%E2%80%93%20but%20on%20instructions%20issued%20internally%20by%20its%20Personnel%20Branch%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Royal%20Navy%E2%80%99s%20practice%20of%20senior%20officers%20carrying%20batons%2C%20on%20the%20grounds%20that%20it%20did%20not%20suit%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98transformed%20navy%E2%80%99%20of%20Amrit%20Kaal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Navy%20Day%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20also%20said%20that%20the%20force%20would%20additionally%20discard%20%E2%80%98vestiges%20of%20the%20colonial%20era%E2%80%99%20by%20%E2%80%98Indianising%E2%80%99%20ranks%20for%20all%20its%20personnel%20below%20officer%20rank%20(PBOR).%20Official%20sources%20said%20some%2065%2C000%20naval%20PBOR%20who%20would%20imminently%20be%20re-designated%20included%20Master%20Chief%20Petty%20Officers%201st%20class%2C%20Master%20Chief%20Petty%20Officers%202nd%20class%2C%20Chief%20Petty%20Officers%2C%20Petty%20Officers%2C%20Leading%20Seamen%2C%20Seamen%201st%20class%20and%20Seamen%202nd%20class.%20Their%20new%20ranks%20were%20yet%20to%20be%20made%20public.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIN%20officers%2C%20will%2C%20for%20now%2C%20continue%20with%20their%20present%20rank%20designations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurthermore%2C%20veterans%20compared%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20public%20announcement%20on%20the%20naval%20epaulette%20change%20to%20the%20subtler%202001%20decision%20by%20Prime%20Minister%20Atal%20Behari%E2%80%99s%20BJP-led%20federal%20coalition%20to%20alter%20the%20naval%20ensign%20to%20divest%20it%20from%20its%20colonial%20origins.%20They%20stated%20that%20at%20the%20time%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20was%20conveyed%20privately%20to%20the%20IN%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20quietly%20executed%20the%20change%20in%20its%20ensign%20in%20which%20the%20George%E2%80%99s%20Cross%20was%20substituted%20by%20the%20IN%E2%80%99s%20crest%2C%20featuring%20an%20Ashoka%20lion%20atop%20an%20elaborate%20anchor%20at%20its%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20three%20years%20later%2C%20in%202004%2C%20the%20naval%20ensign%20reverted%20to%20its%20original%20design%20with%20the%20colonial-era%20George%E2%80%99s%20Cross%2C%20following%20complaints%20that%20its%20blue%20colour%20was%20indistinguishable%20from%20that%20of%20the%20sky%20and%20the%20sea%20and%20ocean.%20The%20ensign%20was%20re-cast%20once%20more%20in%20great%20flamboyance%20by%20Modi%20in%20September%202022%20with%20Shivaji%E2%80%99s%20maritime%20imprimatur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20internal%20service%20matters%20are%20best%20left%20to%20the%20armed%20forces%20themselves%20to%20announce%2C%20as%20declarations%20by%20politicians%20concerning%20them%20give%20rise%2C%20justifiably%20to%20charges%20of%20politicising%20the%20military%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20retired%20one-star%20IN%20officer.%20Yet%20another%20veteran%2C%20also%20declining%20to%20be%20named%2C%20said%20the%20matters%20of%20epaulettes%20and%20re-naming%20naval%20PBOR%20was%20too%20%E2%80%98small%E2%80%99%20an%20issue%20to%20be%20so%20grandiosely%20publicised%20by%20the%20prime%20minister.%20It%20was%20best%20left%20to%20the%20IN%20itself%20to%20make%20public%2C%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESimilar%20efforts%20underway%20in%20the%20army%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20than%20the%20IN%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army%20(IA)%2C%20dating%20back%20to%20the%20era%20of%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20in%20the%2018th%20and%2019th%20centuries%2C%20was%20similarly%20undergoing%20de-colonisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIts%20ethnically%20specific%20regiments%20like%20Sikh%2C%20Gurkha%2C%20Jat%2C%20Kumaon%2C%20Garhwal%20and%20Rajput%2C%20amongst%20others%2C%20were%20likely%20to%20be%20done%20away%20with%2C%20as%20was%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20the%20Commonwealth%20War%20Graves%20Association%20that%20regularly%20honours%201.7%20million%20men%20and%20women%20of%20the%20Commonwealth%20who%20died%20in%20World%20Wars%201%20and%202.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20appraisal%20of%20granting%20honorary%20commissions%20to%20junior%20commissioned%20officers%20in%20the%20rank%20of%20captain%20and%20lieutenant%2C%20and%20the%20continuing%20display%20of%20pre-independence%20battle%20honours%20awarded%20by%20the%20British%20to%20certain%20regiments%20and%20units%20to%20celebrate%20their%20successful%20campaigns%20against%20Sikhs%2C%20Marathas%20and%20the%20Gurkhas%2C%20were%20also%20liable%20to%20be%20scrapped.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERescinding%20the%20long-established%20British%20tradition%20of%20appointing%20one-star%20officers%20and%20above%20as%20%E2%80%98honorary%20colonels%E2%80%99%2C%20or%20%E2%80%98eminence%20grise%E2%80%99%20to%20their%20former%20battalions%20or%20regiments%2C%20in%20recognition%20of%20their%20services%2C%20too%20was%20under%20consideration%2C%20official%20sources%20said.%20And%20like%20IN%20veterans%2C%20retired%20IA%20officers%20also%20believed%20that%20all%20such%20projected%20alterations%20would%20precipitate%20an%20%E2%80%98all-round%20dilution%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20ethos%2C%20as%20tradition%20played%20a%20vital%20and%20dynamic%20role%20in%20military%20life.%20Other%20than%20providing%20continuity%20between%20generations%20of%20soldiers%2C%20it%20also%20bolstered%20morale%20and%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20IA%E2%80%99s%20regimental%20histories%20and%20traditions%20are%20built%20on%20the%20valour%20and%20sacrifice%20of%20generations%20of%20Indian%20soldiers%2C%20irrespective%20of%20under%20whom%20they%20served%20and%20where%20they%20did%20so%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20defence%20analyst%20Major%20General%20A.P.%20Singh%20(retired).%20Doing%20away%20with%20all%20or%20even%20some%20of%20these%20and%20replacing%20them%20with%20something%20new%20and%20untried%20would%20be%20a%20troubling%20transition%20that%20hits%20out%20at%20the%20core%20of%20the%20army%E2%80%99s%20self-esteem%2C%20%3Cem%3Eespirit%20de%20corps%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20overall%20%3Cem%3Ejosh%3C%2Fem%3E%20(fervour)%2C%20the%20former%20armoured%20corps%20officer%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20IA%20veterans%20said%20the%20army%20lived%20by%20the%20credo%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ENaam%2C%20namak%20and%20Nishan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(honour%2C%20loyalty%20and%20identity)%20that%20was%20further%20accentuated%20by%20their%20respective%20units%E2%80%99%20battle%20cry%2C%20all%20of%20which%20were%20rooted%20firmly%20in%20custom%20and%20tradition%20dating%20back%20hundreds%20of%20years.%20%E2%80%9CTo%20tamper%20with%20these%20is%20simply%20to%20deny%20history%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20a%20retired%20three-star%20officer.%20And%2C%20we%20should%20not%20forget%2C%20he%20warned%2C%20that%20today%E2%80%99s%20IA%20is%20the%20sum%20of%20its%20multiple%20parts%20and%20whether%20we%20like%20it%20or%20not%2C%20the%20British%20were%20a%20dominant%20part%20of%20it.%20%E2%80%9CTampering%20with%20history%20is%20avoidable%2C%20as%20the%20prevailing%20system%20has%20worked%20well%20through%20many%20wars%20and%20local%20insurgencies%20since%201947%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20suggested%2C%20adding%20that%20the%20IA%20should%20consult%20with%20veterans%20before%20initiating%20organisational%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20so-called%20colonial%20legacy%20did%20in%20no%20way%20impinge%20upon%20military%20efficiency%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20another%20three-star%20officer.%20Battle%20honours%20honoured%20those%20who%20fought%20shoulder%20to%20shoulder%20for%20a%20just%20cause%20and%20were%20nationalist%20agnostic%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlongside%2C%20the%20IA%E2%80%99s%20eight-odd%20regulation%20officer%20uniforms%20too%20were%20likely%20to%20undergo%20a%20%E2%80%98revision%E2%80%99%2C%20with%20the%20more%20fancy%20and%20colourful%20ones%20with%20British%20overtones%20being%20done%20away%20with.%20These%20included%20the%20dashing%20Blue%20Patrols%2C%20the%20ceremonial%20winter%20uniform%20that%20comprises%20a%20black%20%E2%80%98bandgala%E2%80%99%20coat%20with%20gleaming%20silver-coloured%20buttons%2C%20and%20with%20each%20wearer%E2%80%99s%20rank%20elaborately%20embroidered%20on%20the%20shoulder%2C%20and%20similarly%20coloured%20trousers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22161237%2FIndian_Army-Sikh_Light_Infantry_regiment.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22161237%2FIndian_Army-Sikh_Light_Infantry_regiment.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22161237%2FIndian_Army-Sikh_Light_Infantry_regiment-300x157.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F09%2F22161237%2FIndian_Army-Sikh_Light_Infantry_regiment-1024x534.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-620760%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22626%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESoldiers%20of%20the%20Sikh%20Light%20Infantry%20during%20a%20Republic%20Day%20Parade.%20Photo%3A%20Ant%C3%B4nio%20Milena%2FWikimedia%20Commons%20CC%20BY%203.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVeterans%20spooked%20into%20silence%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20conclusion%2C%20there%20is%20a%20mounting%20conspiracy%20of%20silence%20amongst%20a%20wide%20cross-section%20of%20retired%20service%20officers%20in%20speaking%20to%20the%20media%20on%20military%20and%20security-related%20issues.%20And%20the%20handful%20of%20veterans%2C%20who%20do%20consent%20to%20comment%20critically%20on%20such%20matters%2C%20albeit%20reluctantly%2C%20invariably%20request%20anonymity%20in%20anticipation%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98backlash%E2%80%99%20from%20either%20their%20respective%20service%2C%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20(MoD)%20or%20the%20overall%20national%20security%20establishment%2C%20or%20all%20three.%3C%2Fp%3E%5