.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-spacex-mars-longtermism-baby-sea-turtles-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20weirdo%20millenarianism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20let's%20pause%20for%20a%20moment%20and%20take%20him%20at%20his%20word.%20He%20thinks%20his%20hideously%20complex%2C%20electrically%20powered%2C%20factory-engineered%20technological%20apex%20predator%20will%20not%20only%20continue%20to%20function%20after%20a%20societal%20collapse%20%E2%80%94%20nuclear%20armageddon%2C%20sea-level%20rise%2C%20global%20pandemic%2C%20all%20the%20hits%20%E2%80%94%20but%20actually%20be%20of%20some%20%3Cem%3Euse.%3C%2Fem%3E%20In%20his%20mind%2C%20at%20least%2C%20the%20truck%20will%20get%20us%20where%20we%20need%20to%20go%20long%20after%20there's%20no%20more%20cyber.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20says%20something%20important%20about%20Musk%20and%20the%20flavor%20of%20apocalypse%20he%20thinks%20is%20coming.%20Apparently%20Musk%20believes%20that%20if%20and%20when%20the%20end%20comes%2C%20he%20%E2%80%94%20and%20presumably%20every%20Cybertruck%20owner%20%E2%80%94%20will%20be%20safe%20in%20some%20sort%20of%20armored%20dome%2C%20where%20the%20lights%20are%20still%20on%20and%20the%20champagne's%20on%20tap.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-to-do-survived-the-apocalypse-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20rest%20of%20us%20suckers%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%20Not%20so%20much.%20As%20one%20wag%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsky.app%2Fprofile%2Fcooperlund.bsky.social%2Fpost%2F3kfimpc5eid2a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esnarked%20on%20a%20social%20network%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Musk%20does%20not%20own%2C%20%26quot%3BMusk%20is%20rich%20enough%20that%20his%20conception%20of%20an%20apocalypse%20is%20something%20that%20will%20affect%20normal%20people%20and%20not%20him.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Musk's%20view%20of%20the%20future%20is%20even%20more%20dystopian%20than%20that.%20The%20Cybertruck%20is%20essentially%20built%20for%20postapocalypse%20%3Cem%3