anks%20(SCBs)%20wrote%20off%20nearly%20Rs%2010.6%20lakh%20crore%2C%20with%20almost%20half%20of%20this%20amount%20belonging%20to%20large%20industrial%20houses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApproximately%202%2C300%20borrowers%2C%20each%20with%20loans%20exceeding%20Rs%205%20crore%2C%20deliberately%20defaulted%20on%20around%20Rs%202%20lakh%20crore%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindubusinessline.com%2Feconomy%2Findian-banks-write-off-106-lakh-crore-in-5-years-50-linked-to-large-corporates%2Farticle67604297.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EHindu%20BusinessLine%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20write-offs%2C%20conducted%20in%20accordance%20with%20Reserve%20Bank%20of%20India%20(RBI)%20guidelines%20and%20approved%20bank%20board%20policies%2C%20involve%20removing%20non-performing%20assets%20(NPAs)%20from%20balance%20sheets%20after%20full%20provisioning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSuch%20write-offs%20do%20not%20result%20in%20waiver%20of%20liabilities%20of%20borrowers%20to%20repay%2C%E2%80%9D%20Minister%20of%20State%20in%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%20Bhagwat%20Karad%20said%20in%20a%20written%20response.%20The%20process%20of%20recovery%20of%20dues%20from%20the%20borrower%20in%20written-off%20loan%20accounts%20continues%2C%20write-off%20does%20not%20benefit%20the%20borrower%2C%20Karad%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20newspaper%20reported%20that%20the%20minister%20did%20not%20name%20individual%20borrowers%20whose%20accounts%20have%20been%20written%20off%20citing%20the%20RBI%20Act.%20Quoting%20RBI%2C%20he%20said%20that%20all%20SCBs%20have%20collected%20an%20aggregate%20amount%20of%20Rs%205%2C309.80%20crore%20as%20penal%20charges%2C%20including%20penalty%20charges%20against%20delay%20in%20payment%20of%20loans%2C%20during%20the%20financial%20year%202022-%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%20to%20another%20question%2C%20Karad%20said%20that%20SCBs%20and%20All%20India%20Financial%20Institutions%20report%20certain%20credit%20information%20of%20all%20borrowers%20having%20aggregate%20exposure%20of%20Rs.%205%20crore%20and%20above%20to%20the%20Central%20Repository%20of%20Information%20on%20Large%20Credits%20(CRILC).%20%E2%80%9CAs%20reported%20in%20CRILC%20database%2C%20as%20on%2031.3.2023%2C%20total%202%2C623%20unique%20borrowers%20were%20classified%20as%20wilful%20defaulters%2C%20with%20aggregate%20outstanding%20of%20over%20Rs%201.96%20lakh%20crore%20by%20SCBs%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20also%20clarified%20that%20the%20primary%20regulatory%20objective%20behind%20allowing%20wilful%20defaulters%20to%20enter%20into%20compromise%20settlement%20is%20to%20enable%20multiple%20avenues%20for%20lenders%20to%20recover%20the%20money%20in%20default%20without%20much%20delay.%20Apart%20from%20the%20time%20value%20loss%2C%20inordinate%20delays%20result%20in%20asset%20value%20deterioration%2C%20hampers%20ultimate%20recoveries%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701756934000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16101457%2Frupee-gb36195718_1920.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Findian-banks-write-off-rs-10-6-lakh-crore-in-5-years-mostly-linked-to-large-corporates-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Approximately%202%2C300%20borrowers%2C%20each%20with%20loans%20exceeding%20Rs%205%20crore%2C%20deliberately%20defaulted%20on%20around%20Rs%202%20lakh%20crore.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A181%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbanking%2Findian-banks-write-off-rs-10-6-lakh-crore-in-5-years-mostly-linked-to-large-corporates-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Previous%20decade%20'hottest%20on%20record'%20with%20polar%20ice%20melting%20faster%20than%20in%20the%20last%20century%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701756840000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F12%2F768x432%2Fskynews-ice-s